National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: ORLANDO, FL
Accident Number: MIA89LA001
Date & Time: 10/01/1988, 1030 EDT
Registration: N2628B
Aircraft: ROBINSON R22
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 Minor, 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Instructional
 Analysis WHILE PRACTICING HOVERING THE HELICOPTER BEGAN TO DRIFT.
THE INSTRUCTOR PLT CORRECTED THIS & RETURNED CONTROL TO THE STUDENT PLT.
THE HELICOPTER THEN BEGAN TO DESCEND & THE INSTRUCTOR PLT ATTEMPTED TO CORRECT THIS WITH COLLECTIVE, BUT THE STUDENT PLT APPLIED OPPOSITE COLLECTIVE INPUT.
A SKID CAUGHT THE GROUND & THE HELICOPTER THEN EXPERIENCED DYNAMIC ROLLOVER.
THE STUDENT HAD 7 HOURS OF TOTAL FLIGHT TIME.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: IN FLIGHT COLLISION WITH TERRAIN/WATER Phase of Operation: HOVER Findings 1.
DESCENT - INITIATED - DUAL STUDENT 2.
(C) CONTROL INTERFERENCE - INADVERTENT - DUAL STUDENT 3.
(C) REMEDIAL ACTION - INADEQUATE - PILOT IN COMMAND(CFI) 4.
: 1370 lbs Time Since Last Inspection: Engines: 1 Reciprocating Airframe Total Time:  Engine Manufacturer: LYCOMING ELT: Not installed Engine Model/Series: O-320-B2C Registered Owner: ROTOR FLIGHT, INC.
